00:36:29.766 --> 00:36:35.680
AUDIENCE: You showed the
screenshot of the multi-user VR

00:36:35.680 --> 00:36:36.980
chat.

00:36:36.980 --> 00:36:40.510
How do the-- how does-- how
are the relative positions

00:36:40.510 --> 00:36:43.480
between the multiple
users determined?

00:36:43.480 --> 00:36:44.240
JOHNNY LEE: Sure.

00:36:44.240 --> 00:36:45.380
So that's a good question.

00:36:45.380 --> 00:36:48.320
So each device when
it first boots up

00:36:48.320 --> 00:36:49.790
is its own coordinate frame.

00:36:49.790 --> 00:36:52.810
So what we have is the
area description files,

00:36:52.810 --> 00:36:58.790
which is the pre-existing
coordinate system for the room.

00:36:58.790 --> 00:37:00.590
So by sharing the
area description

00:37:00.590 --> 00:37:03.610
file with multiple devices,
either by pushing those

00:37:03.610 --> 00:37:06.550
over the network or by
copying them manually,

00:37:06.550 --> 00:37:09.550
all the devices will boot up
and localize to the same room,

00:37:09.550 --> 00:37:10.050
essentially.

00:37:10.050 --> 00:37:13.130
AUDIENCE: And that works by
detecting features in the room

00:37:13.130 --> 00:37:17.030
and, like, mapping it to
that relative to the area

00:37:17.030 --> 00:37:17.930
description file, or?

00:37:17.930 --> 00:37:18.680
JOHNNY LEE: Right.

00:37:18.680 --> 00:37:21.140
The area description file
is a visual description

00:37:21.140 --> 00:37:23.800
of the environment which
includes features and matches

00:37:23.800 --> 00:37:24.860
in that space.

00:37:24.860 --> 00:37:29.400
So just like-- it would be
a description of this room.

00:37:29.400 --> 00:37:33.120
And as long as we all shared
the same reference of the room,

00:37:33.120 --> 00:37:36.700
we can all adjust
our coordinate system

00:37:36.700 --> 00:37:38.585
to match the coordinate
system of the room.

00:37:38.585 --> 00:37:39.630
AUDIENCE: Great, thanks.

00:37:39.630 --> 00:37:40.538
JOHNNY LEE: Yep.

